    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-16T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="1064"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1064">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/407.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-16T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1912—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Governor Jalisco will probably resign soon, and Consul Guadalajara requests
                    30,000 rounds ammunition as soon as possible, fearing serious disorder after
                    resignation. War Department is to-day issuing orders for despatch 50,000 rounds
                    to him. If in the meantime the need becomes urgent and the colony at Mexico City
                    can spare the ammunition, have sufficient supplies sent from Mexico City.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
